	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1" facs="EHRI-ET-YV3540639_01.jpg"/>
			<p>Protocol No. 4</p>
			<p>Taken by – <persName ref="#ehri_et_katshikovitsh_pinhas">Katshikovitsh, Pinhas</persName></p>
			<p>Related by <persName ref="#ehri_et_midl">Mrs. Midl</persName> – <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/710400/chortkiv.html"
					>Chortkiv</placeName>, <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/691650/ternopil.html">Tarnopol region</placeName></p>
			<p>Born <date when="1908-10">1908 (October)</date></p>
			<p>In <date when="1941">1941</date>, when the <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_russians">Russian</term>-<term
					ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">German</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1080" type="subject">war</term> broke out, my <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">husband</term> was mobilized into the <orgName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-004583">Soviet military</orgName> and I, with my two <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">children</term> – a <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">daughter</term> aged seven and a <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">boy</term> aged three years old – remained alone,
				living at home in the shtetl of <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/710400/chortkiv.html">Chortkiv</placeName> – western
					<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/690791/ukraine.html">Ukraine</placeName>. I survived innumerable <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-540" type="subject">slaughters</term>.</p>
			<p>The first Jewish <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-132" type="subject">victims</term> in our shtetl fell
				only a few days after the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-633" type="subject">occupation</term> of our
				region by the <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Germans</term>. They ordered a few hundred Jewish <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826" type="subject">men</term> to gather in a square – for <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-943" type="subject">work</term>. The <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826" type="subject">men</term> gathered in the square, but instead of
				taking them to <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-943" type="subject">work</term>, they took them to <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-669" type="subject">prison</term>, and later the <term
					ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Germans</term>, together with the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-637" type="subject">local Ukrainians</term>, <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532" type="subject">murdered</term> them in a brutal fashion. And they
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-563" type="subject">buried some alive</term>. These were the best
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1207" type="subject">people</term> from our city.</p>
			<p>A few days later, we received news from my home town – <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/687826/zalishchyky.html"
					>Zalishchyky</placeName> – five kilometers from us, where my <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822"
					type="subject">parents</term> and <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">sisters</term>
				still lived, that the <orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-350">gestapo</orgName> there had issued an
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-951" type="subject">order</term>: five hundred Jews should come to
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">clean the barracks</term>. If they would not
				heed the command, they would <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532" type="subject">kill</term> all the
				Jews of the shtetl. The <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-951" type="subject">order</term> was fulfilled
				and all five hundred Jews were taken to a place outside the city. They lined them</p>
			<p><pb n="2" facs="EHRI-ET-YV3540639_02.jpg"/></p>
			<p>up ten in a row, one behind the other, and each row was <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532"
					type="subject">shot</term> with one bullet – obviously, from such shooting most were only wounded, and some were not even touched,
				but the <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Germans</term> ignored this and <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-563" type="subject">buried them all alive</term>. Among the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-132" type="subject">victims</term> were my <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">father</term> and my two younger <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">sisters</term> – aged eighteen and twenty years
				old.</p>
			<p>In <date when="1942-03">March 1942</date>, they carried out among us in the shtetl the first formal <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-540" type="subject">slaughter</term>. And immediately after this they
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-951" type="subject">ordered</term> us to move into the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-545" type="subject">ghetto</term>. I went to the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-545" type="subject">ghetto</term> with my <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">children</term>. The <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-831" type="subject">conditions</term> there were terrible, but they did
				not allow us to stay for long in one place. After only six weeks they sent me (together with my <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">children</term>), along with a group of <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">women</term>, to <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/687826/zalishchyky.html">Zalischyky</placeName> .</p>
			<p>After <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-943" type="subject">laboring</term> three months in <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/687826/zalishchyky.html">Zalischyky</placeName>, in <date when="1942-09">September 1942</date> an
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-951" type="subject">order</term> arrived that the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567?dlid=eng" type="subject">camp</term> there must be <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-626" type="subject">free of Jews</term> [<term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-626" type="subject">Judenrein</term>]. Then they sent us to <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/691444/tovste.html">Tovste</placeName> (<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/691444/tovste.html"
					>Toist</placeName>). <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/691444/tovste.html">Tovste</placeName> was an assembly point for the
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532" type="subject">murder</term> of Jews. And we arrived here
				exactly as they were carrying out an <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-529" type="subject"
					>extermination</term>-<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-550" type="subject">aktion</term>. I managed
				to <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-262" type="subject">hide</term>, together with my <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">children</term>. We did not rest for long: in a few
				weeks’ time – it was exactly one day after <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-754" type="subject">Simchat
					Torah</term> – there once again took place here a <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-540"
					type="subject">slaughter</term>, during which over 2,000 Jews were <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532" type="subject">killed</term>. The panic in the city was terrible,
				because no one had imagined that so quickly, after such a short breathing space, another <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-540" type="subject">slaughter</term> would take pace. I <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-262" type="subject">hid</term> in a cellar, together with my <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">children</term> and another seven <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1207" type="subject">people</term>, altogether there were ten of us.</p>
			<p><pb n="3" facs="EHRI-ET-YV3540639_03.jpg"/></p>
			<p>That winter we remained in <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/691444/tovste.html">Tovste</placeName>. In the beginning of <date
					when="1943-03">May 1943</date>, there again took place here a great <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-540" type="subject">slaughter</term>. My <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">family</term>, the three of us, <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-262" type="subject">hid</term> in an attack and thus survived. Lying here
				a few days, my younger <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">child</term> seemed to
				understand the situation and did not even ask for <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-833" type="subject"
					>water</term>.</p>
			<p>During the time in the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-265" type="subject">attic</term> we heard
				heart-rending cries, screams, and calls for help. Many of the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-132"
					type="subject">victims</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-204" type="subject">fled</term>, but the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-637" type="subject">local population</term> – the <term
					ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_ukrainians">Ukrainians</term> – chased after them, beat them, and later <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532" type="subject">murdered</term> them in a terrible fashion. Those few
				Jews who remained alive, in <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-262" type="subject">hiding</term>, were
				later <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-411" type="subject">sorted</term>: the older <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1207" type="subject">people</term> [word missing] were sent to <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/710400/chortkiv.html">Chortkiv</placeName> and the younger to the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567?dlid=eng" type="subject">camps</term>. Together with my <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">family</term>, I <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-204" type="subject">stole out</term> from the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567?dlid=eng" type="subject">camp</term> and night and alone we set out
				for <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/687826/zalishchyky.html">Lysivtsi</placeName>, seven kilometers from <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/691444/tovste.html">Tovste</placeName>. For six weeks it was calm and then they again began a
					Jewish-<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-550" type="subject">aktion</term>. We <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-204" type="subject">fled</term> from the city with a group of <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1207" type="subject">people</term>, but we were noticed by the <term
					ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Germans</term> and they immediately opened fire on us with machine guns. Straight away there
				were 32 <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-132" type="subject">victims</term> from our group. Among them
				was my <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">mother</term>. My <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">daughter</term> was hit by a bullet in her foot, but
				we were already in the field. We <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-262" type="subject">hid</term> among
				the crops until nightfall. At night, with great effort, we returned to <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/691444/tovste.html"
					>Tovste</placeName>. The first <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-280" type="subject">medical
					help</term> that my <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">daughter</term> received was
				from <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-287" type="subject">Doctor</term>
				<persName ref="#ehri_et_greenberg">Greenberg</persName>. And only thanks to the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-287" type="subject">doctor</term>’s extraordinary efforts was it possible
				to save the foot – she only lost her toes.</p>
			<p><pb n="4" facs="EHRI-ET-YV3540639_04.jpg"/></p>
			<p>Later, when the situation in <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/691444/tovste.html">Tovste</placeName> was again in a state of
				tension – we once more left for <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/687826/zalishchyky.html">Lysivtsi</placeName>. In <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/687826/zalishchyky.html">Lysivtsi</placeName> there was still a <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567" type="subject">camp</term> of 200 Jews, who <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-943" type="subject">worked</term> at agricultural labor – the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826" type="subject">men</term> in the stables and the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">women</term> in the fields. We received <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-834" type="subject">food once per day</term>. The <orgName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-004745">Ukrainian police</orgName> would very often fall upon our <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567" type="subject">camp</term> and <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532" type="subject">murder</term> whoever fell into their hands. Likewise
				due to the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-569" type="subject">hunger</term> and terrible <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-831" type="subject">living conditions</term> a <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-493" type="subject">typhus</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-492" type="subject">epidemic</term> broke out – here the <term
					ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_ukrainians">Ukrainians</term> did not take care of the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-292" type="subject">sick</term><note place="bottom">Word missing.</note>
				and anyone who became <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-292" type="subject">ill</term> was immediately
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532" type="subject">murdered</term>.</p>
			<p>No one reacted to all of this, because the law was to beat the Jews. <date when="1944-03-01">March 1, 1944</date>, when the <orgName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-004583">Soviet Armies</orgName> advanced, the <term
					ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Germans</term> and <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_ukrainians">Ukrainians</term> together
				with the <persName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_pers-000419">Vlasovites</persName> became completely wild and
				dealt out <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532" type="subject">murder</term> right and left.</p>
			<p>They caught a Jewish <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">woman</term> from <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/2761369/vienna.html">Vienna</placeName> – Mali – with her <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">son</term> and <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532" type="subject">shot</term><note place="bottom">Should be
					"slaughtered"</note> them. A <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">woman</term> –
				Shechter – from the shtetl – Igolnitz – they <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-562" type="subject">cut
					off</term> her ears and nose and afterwards <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532" type="subject"
					>murdered</term> her. A young <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826" type="subject">man</term> from
					<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/691444/tovste.html">Tovste</placeName> – <persName ref="#ehri_et_rozenstok_isaiah">Isaiah
					Rozenstok</persName> – <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-562" type="subject">they</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532" type="subject">cut off his head</term>; another young <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826" type="subject">man</term> from <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/691444/tovste.html">Tovste</placeName> – <persName ref="#ehri_et_voltshe_malier">Voltshe
					Malier</persName> – they <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-562" type="subject">tied him</term> to a
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-811" type="subject">horse</term> and <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532" type="subject">murdered</term> him together with the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-811" type="subject">horse</term>, they stabbed another middle aged Jew
				from <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/691444/tovste.html">Tovste</placeName> with a <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-562" type="subject">bayonet</term>. A <term
					ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_hungarians">Hungarian</term> Jewish <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-287"
					type="subject">doctor</term> managed to save the last of these.</p>
			<p><pb n="5" facs="EHRI-ET-YV3540639_05.jpg"/></p>
			<p>The few Jews who remained alive – around two hundred – they again gathered them in <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/691444/tovste.html">Tovste</placeName> in the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567" type="subject">camp</term>. For eight days we were watched over by a
				group of old <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Germans</term> – <orgName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-438">Wehrmacht</orgName> – because the young one had been called to the
				front.</p>
			<p><date when="1944-03-23">March 23, 1944</date>, the <orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-004583"
					>Soviets</orgName>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-573" type="subject">liberated</term> our region. We were barley eight
				days with the <orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-004583">Soviets</orgName> when the <term
					ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Germans</term> again renewed their attack and the shtetl once again passed to their
				hands.</p>
			<p>Then, in a <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-831" type="subject">burning frost, starving, exhausted, naked,
					and barefoot</term>, we <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-204" type="subject">fled</term> for 60
				kilometers to <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/710719/chernivtsi.html">Chernivtsi</placeName>. Many of us froze and were left
				on the way.</p>
			<p>We remained in <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/710719/chernivtsi.html">Chernivtsi</placeName> until the end of the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1080" type="subject">war</term>.</p>
